SEARCH
Package gw.rest.core.pl.framework.v1.refs

Class CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver<V extends KeyableBean,A extends KeyableBean>

java.lang.Object
gw.rest.core.pl.framework.v1.refs.CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver<V,A>
Type Parameters:
V - The type of KeyableBean that this resolver resolves to
A - The type of KeyableBean of the ancestor of the resolvedValue and root
All Implemented Interfaces:
JsonValueResolver
public abstract class CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver<V extends KeyableBean,A extends KeyableBean> extends Object implements JsonValueResolver
You may subclass this resolver if you cannot resolve to a KeyableBean based off of id alone, and instead need to pick the KeyableBean from a collection contained on some ancestor entity.

In order for the resolver to work, the schema property must have the x-gw-extensions resourceType set to a resource which is a subtype of DefaultRestElementResource and the path of the updater must resolve to a KeyableBean of type CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver

By default, resolving by both id and refid is supported. You may turn off resolving by refid by adding "setByRefid": false to the updater.

In order for this resolver to work, you must also specify 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' and optionally 'rootToAncestorPath' 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' and 'rootToAncestorPath' must both resolve to a KeyableBean that are the same type and the same as CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver. 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' must start with the special symbol 'resolvedValue' which will be populated with the CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver that is found by the resolver code. And 'rootToAncestorPath' must start with the root on the updater.

If you do not specify 'rootToAncestorPath', then the root of the updater will be used as the ancestor.

    • isEntityViewable

      protected boolean isEntityViewable(V keyableBean)
      Default implementation is true. This should be overridden in subclasses if the developer wishes to add restrictions on whether or not the resolved bean should be visible in the given context.
      Returns:
      false if the given entity should not be visible to the caller and should be treated as not being found, true otherwise

    • getAncestorType

      @NotNull protected abstract @NotNull Class<A> getAncestorType()
      You must implement this method to return the KeyableBean of the ancestor that the resolver works with. This must match the type that is resolved by 'resolvedValueToAncestorPath' and 'rootToAncestorPath' or the root of the updater if no 'rootToAncestorPath' is supplied
      Returns:
      The type of KeyableBean of the ancestor

    • getPossibleResolvedValues

      @NotNull protected abstract V[] getPossibleResolvedValues(A ancestor)
      You must implement this method to return a collection of possible resolved values off of the ancestor. The resolver code will then filter this collection with idMatchExpression(String) to find the correct resolved value
      Parameters:
      ancestor - the ancestor that has access to the collection of possible resolved values. This will be populated by evaluating 'rootToAncestorPath' on the root of the updater. Or will be the root itself if no 'rootToAncestorPath' is supplied
      Returns:
      A collection of CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver's on the ancestor, one of which should be the value we're looking for

    • idMatchExpression

      @NotNull protected abstract @NotNull Predicate<V> idMatchExpression(String id)
      You must implement this method to return a predicate that will filter getPossibleResolvedValues(KeyableBean) to match the 'id' supplied in the JSON payload and return one (or none if none match) valid results. If the 'id' supplied in the json payload fails to match any of the possible values once filtered by the idResolver, then a 400 error will be returned to the caller.
      Parameters:
      id - The 'id' supplied in the JSON payload
      Returns:
      a predicate that uniquely matches the 'id' supplied to a CollectionBasedJsonValueResolver in the getPossibleResolvedValues(KeyableBean) collection
